summary: GLiNER is a compact Named Entity Recognition (NER) model leveraging bidirectional transformers to extract entities of any type efficiently. It outperforms Large Language Models like ChatGPT in zero-shot evaluations while being more resource-friendly, addressing the limitations of traditional NER models and expensive LLMs.
